{
  "stem": "1857.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Otherwise, he was afraid-- he never knew what Leopold could do.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "At that point when Leopold left-- and we were left already, by that time, with older men who were the guards, because all the younger men were sent to the front.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So Schindler felt quite secure.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "A few days before the end of the war, the underground came out-- and I was part of it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we told Schindler like that, 'You tell the guards that if they leave all the weapons, and they leave, we'll let them go.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "If not, the Czech underground and we are going to fight them, and none of them will come out alive.' And Schindler proposed it to the guards, and the guards were more than happy to leave.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They were all older family men, and-- and they knew the war is coming to an end.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They got on trucks and they left.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we were without the guards.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we took over the camp-- the underground.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I got a red band on my arm, and I had a pistol.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I didn't know what to do with it, but I had a pistol.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And at that point, Churchill had the victory speech in England, and Schindler put it on a loudspeaker system in the factory.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Being that I had English lessons before the war for several years-- not that I was that good-- but I was taking lessons all the time in English-- I could understand, hearing the-- what Churchill was saying, and translating it to my friends around me.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And while I was stood there, I just couldn't believe [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that here I am.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The Germans still occupy this part of Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I am listening to-- to Churchill.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
